a gem worth knowing cold. `context.Context` is how Go passes cancellation signals and deadlines through a call chain — first parameter, always:

```go
func DoWork(ctx context.Context) error {
    select {
    case <-ctx.Done():
        return ctx.Err() // cancelled or timed out
    default:
        // do the actual work
    }
}
```

