two goroutines (or threads) each holding a resource the other needs, so both wait forever.

```go
// classic lock ordering deadlock:
var mu1, mu2 sync.Mutex

go func() {
    mu1.Lock(); defer mu1.Unlock()  // grabs mu1, then tries mu2
    mu2.Lock(); defer mu2.Unlock()
}()
go func() {
    mu2.Lock(); defer mu2.Unlock()  // grabs mu2, then tries mu1
    mu1.Lock(); defer mu1.Unlock()
}()
// A holds mu1, wants mu2. B holds mu2, wants mu1. neither moves.
```

the fix: **consistent lock ordering** — always acquire mu1 before mu2, everywhere. alternatively, use `TryLock` with backoff, or restructure so the two resources are never held simultaneously.

